authentic <i>Star Wars</i> prop.

36:38.283 --> 36:39.684
Okay.

36:39.718 --> 36:41.953
I told him that we would never
be able to authenticate it.

36:41.987 --> 36:44.256
So I had to call in
a <i>Star Wars</i> expert.

36:44.290 --> 36:45.791
He could rock some authentication.

36:45.825 --> 36:46.792
Right.

36:46.826 --> 36:48.327
So, um, what you got here?

36:48.361 --> 36:49.962
I brought you my prized possession.

36:49.996 --> 36:51.664
- Your prized possession?
- Yep.

36:51.698 --> 36:54.700
This is my, uh, my lightsaber hilt.

37:03.776 --> 37:05.143
All right, can you tell
me a little bit about it?

37:05.177 --> 37:06.477
You got it at--where
was the shop?

37:06.512 --> 37:07.745
Uh, it was Ann arbor, Michigan.

37:07.779 --> 37:09.613
Uh, the owner got it from an auction

37:09.648 --> 37:12.048
and, uh, it was in the store one
day before I bought it.

37:12.083 --> 37:14.950
It's been on my shelf for,
you know, 15 years, easily.

37:14.985 --> 37:16.318
Okay, Ann arbor, Michigan.

37:16.353 --> 37:18.854
That's a far way from, uh, east
end London, but...

37:18.888 --> 37:20.255
Is that where it was made?
London?

37:20.290 --> 37:21.857
Well they were made in england
but it was filmed in London.

37:21.891 --> 37:23.192
And you say this was in <i>A New Hope?</i>

37:23.226 --> 37:25.227
Yeah, supposedly it was from
the first film, yes.

37:25.261 --> 37:27.196
I paused the movie, like,
time and time again,

37:27.230 --> 37:29.665
just staring at the bottom of
this thing to make sure I had

37:29.699 --> 37:31.467
the right amount
of rubber pieces and, like,

37:31.501 --> 37:33.068
the bottom of it looked correct,

37:33.103 --> 37:34.570
and the right bolt pattern
and everything else.

37:34.604 --> 37:37.173
Uh, the most important thing
about lightsabers is,

37:37.207 --> 37:38.741
obviously, their construction;
What the came from.

37:38.776 --> 37:41.777
They came from what was called
a grey flex flash handle.

37:41.812 --> 37:42.912
You're telling me photographers

37:42.946 --> 37:44.180
would use these things?

37:44.214 --> 37:45.715
This would be used for a
photographer, exactly.

37:45.749 --> 37:46.816
They actually held the flash.

37:46.850 --> 37:48.217
It'd be on a pole and the flash

37:48.252 --> 37:49.218
would be up here.

37:49.253 --> 37:50.220
The production team actually

37:50.254 --> 37:51.221
went out to different antique

37:51.255 --> 37:52.222
shops throughout england and

37:52.256 --> 37:53.223
started buying these things up.

37:53.258 --> 37:54.425
Basically, all the pieces in

37:54.459 --> 37:56.227
the world like this are gonna be found

37:56.261 --> 37:58.162
in a lightsaber because
Lucas went out and bought

37:58.197 --> 37:59.997
every single one of them that
they could possibly get.

38:00.032 --> 38:02.066
- And how do you know that?
- 'Cause I'm a <i>Star Wars</i> geek.

38:02.100 --> 38:03.934
[Laughs]

38:03.969 --> 38:05.636
Another key thing with lightsabers,

38:05.671 --> 38:08.139
this is called
an hp 44 computer board.

38:08.174 --> 38:10.442
This is the on and off button
for a lightsaber.

38:10.476 --> 38:12.811
And it has 13 of these little
slots--is that 13?

38:12.846 --> 38:15.414
- Yeah, lucky 13.
- So there are 13 on there.

38:15.448 --> 38:17.616
A lot of fakes have the wrong number

38:17.650 --> 38:20.418
and, uh, just getting the board
itself would be very hard.

38:20.453 --> 38:22.386
The one thing that kind of makes me

38:22.421 --> 38:24.388
doubt if it's real is its weight.

38:24.423 --> 38:26.023
It's really, really light.

38:26.057 --> 38:29.526
A lot lighter than the ones
that Mark Hamill would use.

38:29.560 --> 38:31.995
However, a lot of cases,
they would make ones

38:32.029 --> 38:33.329
where they would gut the insides,

38:33.364 --> 38:34.831
designed basically
as a stunt lightsaber.

38:34.866 --> 38:35.933
- Mm-hmm.
- Something a lot lighter.

38:35.967 --> 38:37.367
And these would be the ones that

38:37.402 --> 38:38.703
you'd see, like, Mark Hamill
running through the snow.

38:38.737 --> 38:39.871
They didn't want him to fall
on a heavy one.

38:39.905 --> 38:41.006
Right, sure.

38:41.040 --> 38:42.374
Want him to fall on a light one.

38:42.408 --> 38:44.676
What do you think; You think
it's the real deal?

38:44.711 --> 38:47.413
I can tell you this is not an
authentic lightsaber...

38:47.448 --> 38:50.316
From <i>A New Hope,</i>

38:50.351 --> 38:52.452
